@model WBSSLStore.Service.ViewModels.StaticPageViewModel
@{
      var productdetails = WBSSLStore.Web.Helpers.WBHelper.GetProductDetailRows();
    string brand = Model != null && Model.Items != null && Model.Items.FirstOrDefault().Product != null && Model.Items.FirstOrDefault().Product.Brand != null ? Model.Items.FirstOrDefault().Product.Brand.BrandName : "";
    string username = ViewBag.UserName;
}
@section headerTags{
    @Html.Partial("_renderSEO", Model != null && Model.CMSPage != null ? Model.CMSPage : new WBSSLStore.Domain.CMSPage())
}
@Html.Partial("_banner", new Tuple<string, string>("", "SSL Brands"))
<div class="content">
  <div class="wrapper">
    <div class="column3">
      <div class="mobtopcol">
        <div class="column3-2">
          <div class="prodetailswrap marzerotop"> @Html.Partial("_ProdPricing", new Tuple<List<WBSSLStore.Domain.ProductPricing>, List<WBSSLStore.Domain.ProductDetail>>(Model.Items.ToList(), productdetails.ToList())) </div>
          <div class="prodescrip marzerotop">
            <div class="prodescriptxt">
              <h2>Product Description</h2>
              <p>The Thawte Wildcard SSL certificate is one of the premier wildcard certificates available on the market today. It's an excellent certificate for businesses looking to go beyond just encryption for their domain and all accompanying subdomains. That's because this certificate features the reputable Thawte name, a dynamic site seal, and 99.9% browser/mobile recognition – making it one of the most comprehensive wildcard solutions out there. This wildcard is perfect for medium to larger-sized companies, or any business that places the highest stock in their customers' trust and assurance.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div id="cssmenu">
            <ul class="accordion_example">
              <li class="brand-symantec acc_active">
                <div>
                  <p>Assurance &amp; Authentication</p>
                  <div class="clear"></div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <p>Since this is one of the most premium wildcard certificates we have available, it typically takes 2-3 business days to get issued. This is an Organization Validated (OV) certificate, meaning your company will have to complete a light vetting process before the certificate is issued by the Certification Authority (CA). However, there are many benefits to choosing an OV wildcard certificate, the main one being that it will inject <strong>more trust into your website</strong>. The Thawte Site Seal will also be dynamic, with clickable information about your company embedded inside.</p>
                  <div class="clear"></div>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="brand-symantec">
                <div>
                  <p>Security &amp; Encryption</p>
                  <div class="clear"></div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <p>The Thawte SSL wildcard can be issued with the <strong>strongest available encryption strength</strong>, 256-bit. So you can rest assured that you are receiving the highest level of security, if needed, with this premium wildcard certificate.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="brand-symantec">
                <div>
                  <p>SAN &amp; Multi-Domain Support</p>
                  <div class="clear"></div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <p>You can cover one domain and an unlimited amount of subdomains with the Thawte Wildcard SSL certificate. For example, you could assign this certificate to www.domain.com and then mail.domain.com, billing.domain.com, subdomain.domain.com, etc.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="brand-symantec">
                <div>
                  <p>Features &amp; Benefits</p>
                  <div class="clear"></div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <ul class="featurelist">
                    <li>Thawte Wildcard SSL is a fully Business Validated Certificate</li>
                    <li>Secure multiple sites on one physical machine</li>
                    <li>Full business validation</li>
                    <li>Enables 256-bit encryption</li>
                    <li>FREE lifetime, self-service reissues</li>
                    <li>Compatible with 99%+ of all browsers</li>
                    <li>Single root certificate means quick and easy installation</li>
                    <li class="bdrbtm">$1,250,000 warranty</li>
                  </ul>
				  <div class="clear"></div>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="brand-symantec">
                <div>
                  <p>Product Specifications</p>
                  <div class="clear"></div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <ul class="featurelist">
                    <li>Unlimited Sub Domains</li>
                    <li>Issued In 1 to 2 working days</li>
                    <li>Domain and identity authentication and verification</li>
                    <li>Domain name and business name shown on certificate</li>
                    <li>Encryption Strength Up to 256-bit</li>
                    <li>99% Browser Compatibility</li>
                    <li>Support all mobile browsers</li>
                    <li>Site Seal Included</li>
                    <li>Single Server &ndash; Additional server licenses may be purchased</li>
                    <li>Reissue unlimited for the lifespan of the certificate</li>
                  </ul>
				  <div class="clear"></div>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="brand-symantec">
                <div>
                  <p>Site Seal</p>
                  <div class="clear"></div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <p>Websites protected by the Thawte Wildcard SSL certificate will get the reputable Thawte Site Seal displayed on pages of their choosing. This Site Seal is rapidly becoming one of the most trusted across the globe, as your customers will be able to click on it and see your organization details and certificate details. This will help <strong>assure your customers</strong> that you have been vetted by a third party security specialist, and are safe to do business with.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
              <li class="brand-symantec">
                <div>
                  <p>Warranty</p>
                  <div class="clear"></div>
                </div>
                <div>
                  <p>With the Thawte Wildcard SSL certificate, you get a <strong>$1,250,000</strong> warranty. This means that if your site was improperly validated, actually not secured and/or issued to a fraudulent site by this Certificate Authority (CA), etc., Thawte would compensate the end user of the site or victim up to $1,250,000 for any losses or damages incurred. These warranties are there to ensure that your customers are protected and the credibility of the site is established, all in an effort to give users the confidence they need to transact on your site.</p>
                </div>
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
        @Html.Partial("_rightpanel", username) </div>
      <div class="clear"></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
@section Jscripts{ 
<script type="text/javascript">
        $(document).ready(function () {
            // Mobile Menu
            $("#showmenu").click(function (e) {
                e.preventDefault();
                $("#menu").toggleClass("show");
            });
            $("#menu a").click(function (event) {
                event.preventDefault();
                if ($(this).next('ul').length) {
                    $(this).next().toggle('fast');
                    $(this).children('i:last-child').toggleClass('fa-caret-down fa-caret-left');
                }
            });
            $(document).click(function (e) {
                if (!$(e.target).is(".mobmemu, .mobmemu  *")) { $("#menu").toggleClass("hide"); $("#menu").removeClass("show"); }
            });
            $(".accordion_example").smk_Accordion();
        });
    </script> 
} 